              },
              "free_text": [
                " For E > 90 keV (J ~ 1.6 mu-A/cm2)",
                " cross section by the integral method"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "DYNAM"
                ],
                "institute": "2GERBOC"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " For E < 83 keV (J ~ 14 mu-A/cm2)",
                " cross section by the differential method"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Al, Pb, Sb and Sn samples of commercial purity",
                " (99.9% Goodfellow), were implanted with 10 keV 7Li+",
                " ions to fluences of 5 x 10**17, 1 x 10**18 and 2.5 x",
                " 10**18 7Li+/cm2 (the last two fluences only on Al),",
                " using power densities in the range 0.083- 0.33 W/cm2",
                " from a Danfysik 1090 high current ion implanter at the",
                " Ion Beam Laboratory of ITN (Sacavem) Portugal.",
                "Besides the implanted samples, two thin LiF targets",
                " (44 mu-g/cm2 and 30 mu-g/cm2 thick) fabricated by",
                " vacuum-evaporation on a thick Cu and on a self-",
                " supporting Ag backing, were used to measure this",
                " cross section."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " the gamma-rays were detected by means of a",
                " HPGe detector, placed at an angle of 130. degr. to",
                " the beam direction"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The alpha particles produced in the reaction",
                " were detected by means of two PIPS (Passivated",
                " Implanted Planar Silicon Detectors) detectors,",
                " placed at angles (in lab un.) = 124 and 145 deg.",
                " to the beam direction (for E > 90 keV) and four PIPS",
                " detectors placed at angle (in lab un.) = 130 deg.",
                " to the beam direction (for E < 83 keV)."
              ]
            }
          ],
